message.description: A developer-facing error message, such as "not_found". These are stable, and you can develop code that matches against them.

description.description: A human-friendly description for the error. May change at any time.

docsLink.description: A link to the documentation about the error. May change at any time.

ErrorDetail.description: An error returned from a Tesseral API.

iss.description:
Will always be of the form "https://project-xxx.tesseral.app", where
 "project-xxx" is your Project ID.

sub.description: Will always be equal to the `user.id` claim.

aud.description: Will always be equal to the `iss` claim.

exp.description: When this Access Token expires, in seconds since the unix epoch.

nbf.description: When this Access Token was issued, in seconds since the unix epoch.

iat.description: Will always be equal to the `nbf` claim.

organization.description: The Organization the User is logged into.

impersonator.description:
If this is an impersonated Session, this contains information about who on
 your staff is impersonating the user.

AccessTokenClaims.description: The claims encoded in an Access Token.

email.description: The email address of the individual on your staff impersonating the User.

AccessTokenImpersonator.description: Information in an Access Token about who is impersonating the User.

AccessTokenOrganization.description:
Information in an Access Token about the Organization the User is logged
 into.

AccessTokenSession.description: Information in an Access Token about the current Session.

AccessTokenUser.description: Information in an Access Token about the logged-in User.
